description:
This is a 16 minute workout called 'Commit to Fit: Keep Coming Back Strength' from the channel Peter Donohoe.
The workout falls under Strength/Body weight.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Disciplined Grind and The Progression Quest vibe.
The The Disciplined Grind vibe means No excuses, no distractions, just execute. This is especially good for When you want pure focus and efficiency. The The Progression Quest vibe means Methodical, incremental, long-term improvement. This is especially good for Anyone who loves tracking progress and leveling up..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Stay motivated with Pete as your fitness partner leading you through whole body strength exercises including planks, lunges, RDLs, and up-downs. ...
